{"key":"post-14750025","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14750025</id>\n<content>Grains require a casing layer to fruit, and perlite would be no different than placing broken beer bottles on top of your spawn.&amp;nbsp; If you're going to fruit plain grains, use a peat/verm or similar casing layer, and yes it should include gypsum and a buffer such as hydrated lime to prevent trichoderma from attacking the peat moss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For bulk substrates, no casing layer is required or needed if you maintain proper fruiting conditions.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14750107</next>\n<prev>14750013</prev>\n<first>14749372</first>\n<last>14750107</last>\n<when>1310391966</when>\n<utime>07/11/11 04:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}